The paper deals with the fundamental assignment problem in mechanism design, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The problem also involves optimizing welfare and allocation, which are topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also uses probability theory and statistics to analyze the average-case approximation ratio, which falls under information theory (cs.IT).
